:"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/labels/module:forecasting","name":"module:forecasting","color":"35FCCE","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2021-06-13T17:14:16Z","updated_at":"2021-06-21T22:21:38Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"`ForecastingHorizon` currently refuses to take value types with the flag `is_relative=True`.\r\n\r\nInstead, I think it should ask for a compatible `cutoff` and convert the value types to relative with respect to that `cutoff`.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nForecastingHorizon(pd.date_range('1961-01', periods=12, freq='M'), is_relative=True)\r\n```\r\n\r\ncurrently throws an error, but it should be possible to do sth like\r\n\r\n```python\r\nForecastingHorizon(pd.date_range('1961-01', periods=12, freq='M'), is_relative=False, cutoff='1960-12')\r\n```\r\n\r\nand it should be interpreted accordingly.\r\nNote that there does not seem to be a way to define this using `pandas` types, as there is no such thing as a difference type for monthly periods.\r\n\r\nThis could be easily implemented by a call to `to_relative` and `to_absolute`.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/956/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/956/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}